Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘['paikstɑ:f]
*danh từ
 ■cán giáo, cán lao
 ▸plain as a pikestaff
 ■như plain

Anh - Anh
pikestaff
■ noun historical the wooden shaft of a pike.
Phrases
(as) plain as a pikestaff
1》 very obvious.
2》 ordinary or unattractive in appearance. [alt. of as plain as a packstaff, the staff being that of a pedlar, on which he rested his pack of wares.]

sentences.en: It is as plain as a pikestaff.
Their plan is as plain as a pikestaff.
sentences.vi: Kế hoạch của chúng rõ như ban ngày.

sentences.en: That he likes to stay home is as plain as a pikestaff.
sentences.vi: Chuyện thằng bé thích ở nhà rõ như ban ngày.

sentences.en: It's as plain as a pikestaff; this government is ruining the economy.
sentences.vi: Chuyện rành rành ra đó rồi, chính phủ này đang phá hoại nền kinh tế quốc gia.

sentences.en: It's as plain as a pikestaff ; this government is ruining the economy.

sentences.vi: Dễ nhìn thấy rằng chính phủ này hủy hoại kinh tế.

sentences.en: It is as plain as a pikestaff that you are wrong, so no use arguing on.
